1.c: On extreme southeast Corporation line; adjoins Railroad on north.
1.b: Transportation - good streets; church and schools.

areaDesc.5: This is an Italian community. Fairly good neighborhood for lower bracket earners. Poor sales activity. Not much prospect for improvement. Property values remained static past 12 months.

1.c: Some low inland adjacent to area on the north.
1.b: Paved streets; highly restricted; near school; good transportation.

areaDesc.5: This is a relatively new development. All improvements are in: easily accessible; free from smoke and encroachment by industry.

1.c: Railroad runs through center and extreme southeastern part of area; affected by smoke and dirt.
1.b: Good transportation

areaDesc.5: This is an old German settlement slowly declining and being replicated gradually by foreigners and lower wage class American and some negroes. Not far from downtown business section. Property values were static past 12 months.

1.c: Unallotted territory to the south of area appears to retard development somewhat.
1.b: Good transportation

areaDesc.5: Section is in the direction of city's active growth and development; fairly clean neighborhood - suburban territory, homes are well kept. Very few homes in this area prior to 1935. Eight new homes under construction at present.

1.c: During heavy rainfall low point along W. Tuscarawas Street and Banner Avenue will gather surface water.
1.b: Good transportation

areaDesc.5: This area is restricted to residences; adjoins Mt. Marie Academy for girls on W. Tuscarawas; clean neighborhood; spacious lots; pride of ownership is highly evident; area lies west of the Corporation limits. Real estate is active in the west and north-west section in Canton. Entire area contains a mixture of very low and high priced homes side by side.

1.c: Somewhat affected by "Fair Grounds" on west side and Cemetery east of the area
1.b: Good streets; adequate transportation; near schools and churches.

areaDesc.5: Good residential section; within half mile of Myer Lake; clean neighborhood.

1.c: Adjoins West Lawn cemetery on west and water works on east.
1.b: Good transportation - adjoins McKinley monument on north.

areaDesc.5: This is an old neighborhood - a number of lots were cut narrow and short. Area is kept fairly clean - sale demand is only fair.

1.c: Section along North and 6th Street affected somewhat by abandoned factory building.
1.b: Good transportation - good streets - schools and churches - city park - high school

areaDesc.5: Very good residential community and paved streets - pride of ownership. Although area suffers slightly from foreign-born influx, it nevertheless, is a good residential section and sales activities are reported good.

1.c: None
1.b: Good transportation - high school, grade schools and churches; paved streets.

areaDesc.5: More newer homes from Concord Avenue West; new construction is active - good neighborhood - about 15 homes in this section that run slightly over general price range set above. Area contains a mixture of high class and cheaper properties side by side.

1.c: Ajoins industry on southeast - vacant land southwest of area.
1.b: Good transportation - good streets - near schools and park.

areaDesc.5: This is a fairly clean neighborhood - near industry - good location for mill workers.

1.c: Adjoins Pennsylvania Railroad on south, undeveloped territory immediately to the west.
1.b: Good transportation - good streets - restricted neighborhood.

areaDesc.5: This area was developed by the Timken Roller Bearing Company. Due to a housing shortage in Canton and the Company decided to build a number of residences for its employees. Some 250 houses were built here and in area C-10 in 1920. Average price of home in 1920 was $5600. Area is restricted and well kept. Demand is good.

1.c: Adjoins factories on south and east; smoke and dirt.
1.b: Good transportation - schools

areaDesc.5: This was a good neighborhood for the lower bracket earners in the peak years. Slightly better than area "D-2" and "D-5" but heavily populated by foreign-born and is on the downward trend. No improvements in values during past 12 months.

1.c: Adjoins railroad on north and Corporation limits on south and west.
1.b: Good transportation

areaDesc.5: Fairly clean neighborhood - occupied by mill workers - near steel industries and railroads.

1.c: Small factory to south-west of area.
1.b: Good transportation - good streets - schools - church - neighborhood center.

areaDesc.5: Clean neighborhood; pride of ownership. In the southeast section of the city. Surrounded on 3 sides by cheaper property. A "light blue" area. A few cheaper homes on eastern border of area.

1.c: Nominal
1.b: Good transportation - good streets - near schools.

areaDesc.5: Fairly clean laboring section - walking distance to industry. Good location for mill workers. Light sales activity.

1.c: Adjoins industry on the north - Corporation limits on the west.
1.b: Good transportation

areaDesc.5: Heavy foreign population resides here. Poor mortgage risk; cheap neighborhood. Values for both sale and rental have not been increased during next year. Negro population amounts to 15%.

1.c: Adjoins factories on the east; business center of lowest type - dirt and filth and degrading neighborhood.
1.b: Good transportation - near school

areaDesc.5: A good many dilapidated and vacant rooming houses that are uninhabitable. Many vacant store rooms on main streets. This area is occupied by the lowest social class in this city. Very poor sale demand. No increase in values during past 12 months.

1.c: Adjoins light manufacturing on southwest - railroad runs through center of section.
1.b: Good streets - transportation

areaDesc.5: Fairly good section for laboring class. An old American settlement Area is interspersed by small retail business shops. One of the older areas in the city. Values were reported static for past 12 months.

1.c: Adjoins railroad on northwest of area.
1.b: Good streets - transportation - borders the business district on south end.

areaDesc.5: An old community; mixed population; not much demand for homes here. Trend is downward. Fairly good neighborhood for laboring class of people.

1.c: Baltimore and Ohio railroad abutts on west side of area.
1.b: Transportation - good streets - schools and churches; not far from business section of city.

areaDesc.5: This is a fairly old neighborhood adjoining business district. This area is located south of section "B-1". Trend appears slightly downward.

1.c: Adjoins Lake Erie Railroad on east and abutts creek on east.
1.b: Good streets - good transportation - public school - adjoins Nimisilla Park.

2.a: Mill workers; some white collar class

areaDesc.5: Fairly good neighborhood; adjoins business on extreme south end. Occupied mostly by mill workers. Values are returning slowly. Light influx of mixed foreign population.

1.c: None
1.b: Good transportation; excellent school; churches; trees.

areaDesc.5: A relatively new residential section restricted to single dwellings. A clean community; fine homes; pride of ownership. Infiltration of desirable.

1.c: None
1.b: Good roads; highly restricted.

areaDesc.5: This is the best class "A" residential in Canton; 90% homeowners; many new homes under construction. Pride of ownership is highly evident; free from smoke, dirt and industry encroachment.

1.c: None
1.b: Good transportation - near to schools and churches adjacent to park system; restricted neighborhood.

areaDesc.5: Good residential section; pride of ownership; near business district; homes are kept in good repair. Sale prices are advancing. Employment among people in this area good. One of the older residential sections but demand is still good. Unable to make fiber breakdown of this area because of mixture of cheaper homes side by side with higher priced properties.

1.c: Nominal
1.b: Good streets - good transportation - schools and churches; public park south of area.

areaDesc.5: Somewhat smaller and cheaper homes in northeastern section of area. It is, however, a good area for mill workers. Near to industry - fairly clean neighborhood.

1.c: Adjoins factory on south - Area is affected somewhat by smoke and dirt.
1.b: Good transportation - near schools, both Public and Parochial.

areaDesc.5: Fairly good location for cheaper type of labor. A mixed foreign community. Negroes constitute 5% of community. Slight increase in scale and rental values during past 12 months.

1.c: Railroad shop is 1/2 mile south of area.
1.b: Community church and school - addition is well planned - restricted - good transportation.

areaDesc.5: Section south of Mahoning Road is less built up and values are slightly cheaper; foreign population concentrated south of Mahoning Road.

1.c: Adjoins factory on north and railroad on northeast; also scattered factories through area.
1.b: Transportation - schools and church

areaDesc.5: This is a colored section - lower class of Jews and Italians - old section of the city. No demand for sales. No increase in sale or rental values during past 12 months.
